Pediatric patients may be more susceptible to systemic toxicity from use of topical corticosteroids. [see


                              Use in Specific Populations (8.4)
                           ]

Topically applied clobetasol propionate cream, 0.05% (emollient) can be absorbed in sufficient amounts to produce systemic effects [see


                        Warnings and Precautions (5.1)
                     ].
